{{for|other amusement parks known by the same name|Luna Park}}
'''Luna Park''' was an amusement park in [[St. Petersburg]], Russia that was open to the public from 1912 to 1924. Patterned after [[Luna Park, London|its London namesake]] (which itself was patterned after the [[Luna Park, Coney Island (1903)|Coney Island]] and [[Luna Park, Pittsburgh|Pittsburgh]] [[Luna Park]]s), it was Russia's first amusement park. After its permanent closure in 1924, Luna Park's grounds became the site of the stadium at [[Saint Petersburg State University]].

