{{Infobox NRHP | name = Terrell Jacobs Circus Winter Quarters | nrhp_type = hd | nocat = yes | image = Circus Drive-In near Peru.jpg | caption = Circus Drive-In, July 2012 | location= 6125 US 31 South near [[Peru, Indiana|Peru]], [[Pipe Creek Township, Miami County, Indiana]] | coordinates = {{coord|40|40|36|N|86|07|38|W|display=inline,title}} | built = c. {{Start date|1939}}-1967 | locmapin = Indiana#USA | architect = Stuber, Jack; Burke, C.J. | architecture = | added = April 5, 2012 | area = {{convert|11.5|acre}} | governing_body = Local | refnum = 12000188<ref name="nps">{{cite web|url=http://www.nps.gov/nr/listings/20120413.htm|title=National Register of Historic Places Listings|date=2012-04-13|work=Weekly List of Actions Taken on Properties: 4/02/12 through 4/06/12|publisher=National Park Service}}</ref> }}
'''Terrell Jacobs Circus Winter Quarters''', also known as Pipe Creek Wild Animal Farm and Circus Winter Headquarters, is a historic [[circus]] complex and national [[Historic district (United States)|historic district]] located at [[Pipe Creek Township, Miami County, Indiana|Pipe Creek Township]], [[Miami County, Indiana]]. The district encompasses five contributing buildings, three contributing sites, three contributing structures, and seven contributing objects related to the circus headquarters. Most notable are the Terrell Jacobs Cat Barn (1939, 1951), Terrell Jacobs Elephant Barn (1945, 1950), and the Circus Drive-In Restaurant (1967). Other notable contributing resources are the Elephant Rock (1901, 1940), Jacobs Bridge (c. 1940), six Cole Brothers Circus Wagons (c. 1950), creek landscape and Wallace Grotto (1944-1949), and the wild animal graveyard (c. 1945-1970). The property was the site of the birth of [[Captive white tigers#Tony.2C Bagheera.2C and Frosty: A new strain|Tony]], a captive white tiger.<ref name="SHAARD">{{cite web| url = https://secure.in.gov/apps/dnr/shaard/welcome.html| title = Indiana State Historic Architectural and Archaeological Research Database (SHAARD) | publisher = Department of Natural Resources, Division of Historic Preservation and Archaeology | format = Searchable database| accessdate = 2016-05-01}} ''Note:'' This includes {{cite web| url =https://secure.in.gov/apps/dnr/shaard/r/29876/N/Terrell_Jacobs_Circus_Winter_Quarters,_Miami_Co.pdf| title = National Register of Historic Places Inventory Nomination Form: Terrell Jacobs Circus Winter Quarters| accessdate = 2016-05-01| author=Kurt West Garner| format = PDF| date=November 2011}} and Accompanying photographs.</ref>
It was listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 2012.<ref name="nps"/>
